Class
Description
Album
Class responsible for simulating an album
Componets
Class responsible for having a standard setting to be applied in the view's screen.
Config
Interface responsible for having the signature of the setting's constants that will be implemented to build the screens.
CupSticker
Class responsible for simulating Cup sticker and is inherited from the class Sticker
DcSticker
Class responsible for simulating a DC sticker and is inherited from the class Sticker
LoadData
Class responsible for simulating a database of both Cup and DC stickers that exists in an album
Main
Class responsible for the main flow of the project
MainScreen
Class responsible for implementing the interface Config, inherits the JFRame class and makes possible the manufacture of the main screen so that the user can interact with the view through the actions provided by the panels, components and its events
Sticker
Abstract class responsible for simulating a sticker.
Sticker.Code
 
StickerScreen
Class responsible for implementing the interface Config, inherits the JFRame class and makes possible the manufacture of the sticker screen so that the user can interact with the album through the actions provided by the cards, buttons and its events.
User
Class User simulates a behavior of an user that has an album and is a holder of it
